The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Khedira to join Real
                                                                                                                       7                                      Khedira to join Real
                      
	Berlin: Germany midfielder Sami Khedira, who played a major part in Germanys progress to the World Cup semi-finals, is to join Real Madrid from VfB Stuttgart, the Bundesliga club said on Friday.         
	VfB and Real Madrid have agreed on the midfielders move to the Spanish capital, the German club said on their website. As soon as the German international has passed a medical exam, he will put his signature on the contract.         
	VfB, where Khedira made his professional debut in 2006, said they were sorry to let the 23-year-old go.One is always extremely unhappy to let go a player who dictates the game and is easily identified with, such as Sami Khedira, said Stuttgarts sporting director Fred Bobic. (Reuters)                                                                                                                     
